ext\\n\\nThe Slack notification steps were just added to `e2e-triage.yml`. Reviewing them for correctness and robustness reveals three issues, one of which is a real bug.\\n\\n## Issues Found\\n\\n### 1. JSON injection in Slack payload (BUG)\\n\\n**File:** `.github/workflows/e2e-triage.yml:130`\\n\\nThe \\\"Notify Slack - triage complete\\\" step interpolates `${{ steps.slack-summary.outputs.message }}` directly into a JSON string. The summary message contains:\\n- Literal newlines (from `echo -e` expanding `\\\\n`)\\n- Slack mrkdwn with `*bold*`, `<url|text>`, special chars\\n- Test names, URLs, agent names\\n\\nAny `\\\"` or unescaped newline in the output breaks the JSON payload, causing the step to fail silently.\\n\\n**Fix:** Build the complete JSON payload in the \\\"Build Slack summary\\\" step using `jq` (which handles JSON escaping correctly), write it to a file, and use `payload-file-path` instead of `payload` in the Slack action.\\n\\n### 2. Missing webhook guard on \\\"triage complete\\\" step\\n\\n**File:** `.github/workflows/e2e-triage.yml:117-118`\\n\\n\\\"Notify Slack - triage started\\\" (line 47) checks `secrets.E2E_SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL != ''` before running. \\\"Notify Slack - triage complete\\\" (line 118) only has `if: always()` — it will fail if the secret isn't configured.\\n\\n**Fix:** Change to `if: ${{ always() && secrets.E2E_SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL != '' }}`.\\n\\n### 3. Same guard needed on \\\"Build Slack summary\\\" step\\n\\n**File:** `.github/workflows/e2e-triage.yml:89`\\n\\nThe \\\"Build Slack summary\\\" step runs `jq` and builds the message. It's wasted work when no webhook is configured. Add the same guard.\\n\\n**Fix:** Change to `if: ${{ always() && secrets.E2E_SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL != '' }}`.\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n### `.github/workflows/e2e-triage.yml`\\n\\n1. **\\\"Build Slack summary\\\" step** — rewrite to output a JSON file instead of a multiline string:\\n   - Use `jq` to construct the full Slack Block Kit payload (properly JSON-escaped)\\n   - Write to `slack-payload.json` in the workspace\\n   - Add `if: ${{ always() && secrets.E2E_SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL != '' }}`\\n\\n2. **\\\"Notify Slack - triage complete\\\" step**:\\n   - Switch from `payload:` to `payload-file-path: slack-payload.json`\\n   - Add fallback: if `slack-payload.json` doesn't exist (build step failed), use a static error payload\\n   - Add `if: ${{ always() && secrets.E2E_SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL != '' }}`\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. Create a sample `triage-summary.json` with edge-case content (quotes, special chars in test names) and run the `jq` commands locally to verify valid JSON output\\n2. Verify the YAML parses correctly with `actionlint` or by viewing in GitHub Actions UI\\n\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"9d2cb3ff-cb5e-42dc-bcb1-deb15e01c7f4\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"c3e1e13a-945a-4bea-8a6b-ad20b95668e3\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"main\",\"slug\":\"sequential-stargazing-twilight\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01B276wuGgzqSMkoey4hG8Cd\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"Let me start by reading the current workflow file to understand the existing code.\",\"signature\":\"\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":25778,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":25778},\"output_tokens\":9,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYnRq2VRo9v6vo4XfHaeB\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"3a21cd08-e753-47ba-b4f2-68e571bc2ce3\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-06T20:06:34.242Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"3a21cd08-e753-47ba-b4f2-68e571bc2ce3\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"c3e1e13a-945a-4bea-8a6b-ad20b95668e3\",\"ve